parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction or failure of the airbag system can lead to the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of an accident, resulting in serious injury or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag warning light comes on
the airbag warning light flashes continuously
the side curtain airbag deploys spontaneously
the airbag system fails to deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loosening of the fuel pressure sensor can cause a fuel leak, which can lead to a fire hazard, accidents, or serious injury.
symptoms: Intermittent gasoline smell outside the vehicle
fuel leak
fuel pressure sensor not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause a fuel leak, which can lead to a fire hazard, accidents, or serious injury.
symptoms: Intermittent gasoline smell outside the vehicle
fuel leak
fuel pump not functioning properly
vehicle unable to run due to fuel leak.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the viscous cooling fan clutch can cause the vehicle to move forward on its own while stopped, potentially leading to accidents, and also puts significant load on the engine, causing power loss to the drivetrain.
symptoms: The engine RPM surges
especially with the AC on
causing the RPM to increase from around 500 to 1000 RPM
which can move the vehicle forward at a stop unless the brake is firmly pressed. The issue is more frequent and significant in hot weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to inconvenience, safety risks, and potential accidents, especially if the vehicle stalls while in motion.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to start
the vehicle stalls while driving
no warning lights are illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The disintegration of the high-pressure fuel cap can cause metal fragments to enter the engine, leading to engine damage, stalling, or failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Abnormal sounds coming from the vehicle
metal fragments in the engine
engine damage or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The premature failure of the catalytic converters can cause the check engine light to come on, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing damage to the vehicle's engine and other components.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the vehicle's engine performance is affected
the vehicle may experience decreased fuel efficiency
and the vehicle may emit excessive emissions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine starting issue can cause inconvenience, anxiety, and potentially leave the driver stranded, especially if it occurs in a hazardous location.
symptoms: The engine fails to start occasionally
the vehicle may require jump-starting
the battery may be drained
and the issue may be intermittent and difficult to diagnose.
